"I saw you on <i>Endless Pranks Grand Prix</i>."

53
00:04:19,592 --> 00:04:23,563
Things like that
have never happened before,

54
00:04:23,630 --> 00:04:25,265
so it was a bit surprising.

55
00:04:25,331 --> 00:04:27,467
I'm grateful for the opportunity.

56
00:04:29,102 --> 00:04:34,207
<i>Expanding his activities to variety TV
has had a synergistic effect.</i>

57
00:04:36,909 --> 00:04:42,515
{\an8}"SHIMAUMA PRINT" COMMERCIAL

58
00:04:45,985 --> 00:04:50,290
The same vibe, but could you
do your pose a bit lower?

59
00:04:51,591 --> 00:04:56,162
<i>He landed his first
solo commercial appearance.</i>

60
00:05:00,733 --> 00:05:05,004
<i>His comical appeal
became a part of his strength.</i>

61
00:05:06,973 --> 00:05:10,109
It's a sort of surreal comical touch.

62
00:05:10,877 --> 00:05:13,112
I think I exude a strangeness,

63
00:05:13,179 --> 00:05:15,915
so I want to try and do more of that.

64
00:05:18,818 --> 00:05:24,023
{\an8}<i>Repeatedly challenging yourself
is something Shori Sato is doing as well.</i>

65
00:05:26,392 --> 00:05:30,163
{\an8}<i>On this day, he acted in a short drama
for a variety program.</i>

66
00:05:31,698 --> 00:05:37,170
It's different from usual in that
I have to represent the group.

67
00:05:37,236 --> 00:05:40,106
I really enjoy doing variety programs.

68
00:05:40,773 --> 00:05:43,810
Trying new things
is really important to me.

69
00:05:43,876 --> 00:05:45,645
Especially these days.

70
00:05:45,712 --> 00:05:47,447
Aah.

71
00:05:48,314 --> 00:05:51,818
<i>He plays a loser with an Oedipus complex.</i>

72
