University, yes.

86
00:06:53,312 --> 00:06:56,215
This is about Brexit.

87
00:06:56,282 --> 00:07:00,253
It's about Britain leaving the EU.

88
00:07:00,319 --> 00:07:04,157
We have discussions.
It's a kind of seminar course.

89
00:07:05,525 --> 00:07:08,027
<i>Marius debuted as
an elementary school student,</i>

90
00:07:08,594 --> 00:07:10,897
<i>but now he's a third year in university.</i>

91
00:07:11,431 --> 00:07:13,933
It's "How do democracies die?"

92
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:16,636
It's interesting, really. I like it.

93
00:07:17,236 --> 00:07:22,175
I want to use my position
as an idol to inspire people

94
00:07:22,241 --> 00:07:27,013
to learn about government
and the world and get more interested.

95
00:07:28,114 --> 00:07:31,284
{\an8}<i>On this day, he had
a recording for a quiz show.</i>

96
